&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;At the core of our business is our commitment to understanding our clients&#39; needs, challenges, and opportunities. As a member of our team, you&#39;ll be at the forefront of emerging trends and technologies by working closely with clients to position our products and services in a way that helps them achieve their goals. You will enjoy access to extensive training and development opportunities, including ongoing coaching and mentorship from experienced sales professionals. We are committed to helping you achieve your personal and professional goals, and we can’t wait for you to join the team!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;PitchBook’s Core Sales team drives our growth through new client acquisition in partnership with the Sales Development team and Business Development Associate team. Our Business Development Core reps oversee the sales process from product demonstration to deal closure. They are experts in demonstrating to our clients why their businesses cannot live without PitchBook. This is a highly visible team that makes a direct and significant impact on our business.    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Business Development Representative, Core Sales works diligently to close new business opportunities provided by Sales Development Representatives, Business Development Associates, or through their own prospecting. This role contributes to PitchBook’s overall sales goals by managing clients through the sales cycle from product demonstration to deal close. PitchBook’s Business Development Representative, Core Sales manages a robust sales pipeline to grow the PitchBook client portfolio.  &lt;/span&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;
